comments.text:
The test checks the execution order of two async scripts, where one of them is served with 2 second delay.

Could this have been caused by bug 1053321 which concerns preloading of async (and defer) scripts and landed shortly before this test started failing?  It looks like that patch could change the order of preloaded scripts.

comments.author: honzab.moz@firemni.cz

comments.text:
Has this started with this https://hg.mozilla.org/integration/mozilla-inbound/rev/de253c53864457e3879dd405212e368ec77ddfb2 ?  (Doesn't seem related)

The delay is made by the WP test server via the "?pipe=trickle(d2)" query?

Just a note that the test is probably total bogus.  There is no guarantee that the response will come in the expected order from the server however delayed it can be!  Never make that assumption when writing a test!

Anyway, just for curiosity and because this has happened quite often on https://treeherder.mozilla.org/#/jobs?repo=mozilla-inbound&revision=de253c53864457e3879dd405212e368ec77ddfb2&filter-searchStr=bd70ca93e21233a00b03fb31854793569e6ec457 I would be interested in MOZ_LOG=sync,timestamp,nsHttp:5 log.  

I probably won't have time to investigate this tho during tomorrow.
